le="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ent Decision (FID) enabling CfD so that it can make a Final Investment Decision at </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the end of 2015.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:15pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Executive Summary</span></li></ol><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:15pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">CCS is a technically viable, proven technology ready to be deployed at scale today.  The lack of the policy incentive required by</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, and already available to,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">other </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">renewable and low-carbon energy technologies is what has delayed deployment of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">CCS </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in the UK.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  This ought to be remedied by the introduction of the Contract for Difference mechanism as part of the Energy Market Reform process but it remains to be seen if CfDs for CCS can provide risk sharing appropriate for a technology in the early stages of depl</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">oyment and if the CfD is bankable.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:15pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Carefully developed CCS projects </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">already </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">have the potential to be cost competitive (on a cost per unit of electricity basis) with other more mature renewable and low-carbon technologies such as offshore wind.  </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:15pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Using the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">captured CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> for Enhanced Oil Recovery (EOR) and storage</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> brings additional benefits such as a low, or zero, cost storage, additional taxation revenue from incremental oil production; and the employment and security of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">energy </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">supply benefits of extending th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e life of declining North Sea oil fields.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  2Co’s strategy is founded in a resolute belief that EOR is a critical value driver in establishing a vibrant CCS industry.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:15pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Further cost efficiencies can come from realising the economies of scale that come from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">enabling cluster of projects such as White Rose and Don Valley in Yorkshire.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:15pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">CCS is an essential technology if the UK is to meet its legally binding CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> emissions reduction targets.  It is the route fossil fuelled power generation (coal and natural gas) ca</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">n take </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> remain a part of the UK’s low-carbon power generation mix</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> in the future.  </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:15pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Numerous studies have shown that trying to deliver targeted CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><sp