e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> technologies is ready to be deployed at scale today.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Experience of deployment of the technologies will be the best way to identify the areas that will benefit most from further research and development.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Further substantial volumes of CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> can be captured</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> from energy intensive industrial sectors such as steel and cement.  Some sectors, such as gas processing and ammoni</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a production, already separate </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and capture CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> as part of the industrial process and the additional costs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> represent very low cost CCS opport</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">unities. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> 2Co looks for</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ward to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> opportunities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to be the offtaker of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">additional </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">volumes of CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:1